a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes mean :: "real"
assumes h0 : "mean = (70 + 80 + 90 + 75 + 80 + 85) / 6"
shows  "mean = 80"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Points earned on equally weighted tests are 70, 80, 90, 75, 80 and 85. What is the mean of these six test scores? The final Answer is 80
 ### Proof
 We take the average of these six scores: \begin{align} \frac{70 + 80 + 90 + 75 + 80 + 85}{6} &= \frac{(70 + 90) + 80 + 80 + (75 + 85)}{6}\\ &= \frac{(80 + 80) + 80 + 80 + (80 + 80)}{6}\\ &= \frac{6\cdot 80}{6}\\
 &= \boxed{80}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes mean :: "real"
assumes h0 : "mean = (70 + 80 + 90 + 75 + 80 + 85) / 6"
shows  "mean = 80"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the mean (average) of the numbers 70, 80, 90, 75, 80, and 85. The final answer is 80.
